# Engineering Routing

- Start with `Senior Architect` for major feature work, data-flow changes, or anything that changes boundaries across `app/`, `src/context/`, `src/services/`, or `app/api/`.
- Use `Senior Frontend` for UI-first changes in `app/**/*.tsx`, `src/components/**/*`, `src/context/**/*`, and UX work around loading, accessibility, navigation, or rendering.
- Use `Senior Backend` for API and integration work in `app/api/**/*`, `lib/**/*`, `src/services/**/*`, and `src/repositories/**/*`.
- Use `Senior Fullstack` when a feature crosses UI, session state, and API boundaries in one slice.
- Keep one primary lens per thread. If a change is deep on both UI and API, split it into separate frontend and backend passes after the architecture pass.
- Before merge, run the supporting lenses that fit the change: `Senior Security`, `Senior SecOps`, `Senior QA`, `Code Reviewer`, and `Senior DevOps`.
- Name the lens in the first line of the prompt so the intended rule is explicit.
